      <div class="bio-content">
        <h1>South China Tiger</h1>
        <p class="status critically-endangered big">Critically Endangered</p>
        <p><strong>Estimated remaining:</strong> Extinct in the wild</p>

        <h3>Habitat</h3>
        <p>Historically inhabited forests and mountains of central and eastern China. Currently survives only in captivity with reintroduction efforts planned for suitable protected areas.</p>

        <h3>Threats</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Historical persecution as "pests"</li>
          <li>Massive habitat loss during 20th century</li>
          <li>Extreme population fragmentation</li>
          <li>Lack of genetic diversity in captive population</li>
          <li>Difficulty establishing viable wild populations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Conservation efforts</h3>
        <p>Captive breeding programs in Chinese zoos and South Africa's Laohu Valley Reserve. Preparation of potential reintroduction sites in China. Genetic management to maintain diversity. Training captive-born tigers for eventual wild release through rewilding programs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
